          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is dedicated to a regional form of the Hindu deity Viṣṇu called Dattātreya, particularly popular in Maharashtra and associated with elements of Vaiṣṇava-tantra. There is a note on the front of the manuscript (f. 1r) listing the five prāṇas (breaths), used in ritual respiratory exercises.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Dattātreyastotra</title>
              <title type="vernacular">दत्तात्रेयस्तोत्र</title>
              <author>
                <persName type="authority">Śaṃkarabhagavatpāda</persName>
              </author>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīmatparamahaṃsaparivrājakācāryaśrīmadgovindoviṃdabhagavatpūjyapādaśiṣyaśrīmacchaṃkarabhagavatpādaviracitaṃ śrīmaddattātreyastotraṃ saṃpūrṇaṃ // śrīvāsūdevārpaṇamastu // (f. 2r).</colophon>
